conclusion: To determine if Car A is ahead of or behind Car B at \(t = 10s\), analyze their positions on the v-t graph.
The image shows a v-t graph with two lines, A and B, representing the velocity of Cars A and B over time.
Line A is horizontal at 40 m/s from \(t = 0s\) to \(t = 20s\), and then decreases linearly to 0 m/s by \(t = 30s\).
Line B is a straight line starting at 0 m/s and increasing linearly to 40 m/s by \(t = 30s\).
At \(t = 10s\), Car A has a velocity of 40 m/s and Car B is accelerating from 0 m/s.
Since Car A's velocity is 40 m/s at \(t = 10s\) and Car B is still accelerating, Car A is moving faster.
Given the same initial velocity, the distance traveled at \(t = 10s\) is the same for both cars.
Since Car A is traveling at a higher velocity, it is ahead of Car B.
Car A is ahead of Car B at \(t = 10s\).
